    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-21T02:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-21T02:30:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/7–2151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-21T13:00:00+05:30"
                            >July 21, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 66, July 19. The suggestions for
                    a course of action contained in <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> appear
                    to proceed from the assumption of great danger of outbreak of gen hostilities
                    between Ind and <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>, and that this is principal
                    danger in present situation, It seems to Emb that greatest immed danger lies in
                    possibility of outbreak of communal rioting (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 50, July 17), and that a debate in <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> at this time with inevitable hardening of position on both sides
                    and consequent <pb facs="0324" n="1788" xml:id="pg_1788"/> newspaper polemics
                    and heightened public emotion, wld increase the risk that communal disorders wld
                    take place.</p>
                <p>Restraining pressure shld be brought to bear on two <gloss target="#t_PM1"
                        >PM</gloss>’s, but it shld be exercised privately and not in public. I
                    recommend that US and UK take appropriate action independently and not jointly
                    and I suggest US take initiative in addressing both <gloss target="#t_PM1"
                        >PM</gloss>’s.</p>
                <p>I communicated substance <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> to Graham last
                    night, but because of pressure of his engagements then and today he has not yet
                    had sufficient time to give consideration to subj.</p>
                <p>Rptd info London 10, New Delhi 12, Canberra 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
